Patients with AD are hyperinsulinemic and hyperglycemic compared to healthy control individuals (Razay and Wilcock, 1994<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">). Cell culture studies suggest that insulin accelerates trafficking of Ass from the Golgi and trans-Golgi network to the membrane and thus accelerates the release of Ass into the extracellular fluid (Gasparini et al., 2001<IMG BORDER=1 WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=7 ALT="Go"
SRC="/icons/fig-down.gif">). Furthermore, increased insulin levels may also interfere with the clearing of Ass because both are proteolyzed by insulin degrading enzyme
